      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) SAR reasoning (why these features matter for CYP2D6 inhibition)\nCYP2D6\u2019s active site commonly favors ligands that can form a strong **ionic interaction** with an acidic residue (often described as **Asp301**) via a **protonated amine**, plus hydrophobic/aromatic contacts.",
