      "content": "## 3) Mechanistic basis (how it would interact with CYP2D6)\n- Likely binds (if at all) through **hydrophobic/aromatic stacking** and shape complementarity.\n- Could act as a **weak, nonspecific CYP binder** (potentially affecting other CYPs that are more driven by lipophilicity, e.g., CYP3A4), but for **CYP2D6 specifically**, the lack of a **protonated amine** reduces binding affinity and inhibitory potency.\n- No obvious **mechanism-based inhibition (MBI)** alert (e.g., methylenedioxyphenyl, terminal acetylenes, anilines prone to reactive intermediates) from the provided structure.",
